"title": "8711: covenant breakers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8711: covenant breakers",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Covenants were central to OT life, with the result that those who broke covenants, and especially those who violated the covenant between God and Israel, were regarded as a serious threat to social stability.</p>\n<h2>The importance of covenants</h2>\n<h3>The covenant between God and his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:16\">GEN 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:5\">2SA 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:5\">ISA 24:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:3\">ISA 55:3</a></p>\n<h3>God will remain faithful to his covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:1\">JDG 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:8\">PSA 105:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:10\">ISA 54:10</a></p>\n<h2>Covenants between people</h2>\n<h3>Covenants made in the sight of God were permanently binding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:16-1Sam23:18\">1SA 23:16–23:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:21\">DEU 23:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:4\">ECC 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Condemnation of those who break covenants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:7\">HOS 6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:17\">PRO 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of covenants between people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:27\">GEN 21:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:24\">JOS 24:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:12\">1KI 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:34\">1KI 20:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:8\">JER 34:8</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of breaking the covenant with God</h2>\n<h3>Coveting the possessions of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:4\">ECC 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:17\">EXO 20:17</a></p>\n<h3>Stealing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:15\">EXO 20:15</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:19\">DEU 5:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:24\">DEU 23:24</a></p>\n<h3>Using dishonest weights or scales</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:35-Lev19:36\">LEV 19:35–19:36</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:7-Hos12:8\">HOS 12:7–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Moving boundary stones</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:10\">PRO 23:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:14\">DEU 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:17\">DEU 27:17</a></p>\n<h3>Extortion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:6\">HAB 2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:2\">ISA 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:12\">EZK 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11\">AMO 5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Breach of trust</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:2\">LEV 6:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:17\">EZK 16:17</a></p>\n<h3>Not repaying loans</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:21\">PSA 37:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Not paying fair wages</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:6-Gen31:9\">GEN 31:6–31:9</a></p>\n<h3>Failing to care for aliens</h3>\n<p>Aliens living in Israel were regarded as having privileged status amongst Gentiles, and were treated as covenant people in some respects:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:9-Deut29:15\">DEU 29:9–29:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:12\">DEU 31:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:33-Josh8:35\">JOS 8:33–8:35</a></p>",
